03/06/2003
KIEV, Ukraine -- The chairmen of the Bulgarian and Ukrainian parliaments, Ognyan Gerdjikov and Volodymyr Lytvyn, signed a co-operation protocol on Monday (2 June), which aims to enhance the collaboration between the two countries' legislative branches. The two officials discussed reforms and co-operation in the NATO integration process. Lytvyn said the two sides should boost co-operation in all sectors, but should focus on trade and economic ties. The two countries' prime ministers are to meet this fall. (UNIAN - 02/06/03)
